RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOIRA was forced in a bit by an outside foe after the opening furlong, switched outside that one and settled down racing last but one and off the inside, began to edge closer on the turn three wide, was niggled along just a bit past at the half and moving out four deep, swept five then six wide leaving the bend and struck the lead by the top of the stretch, drifted in at that juncture while clear and under urging, spurted away and extended the margin under steady handling. SKIMS (GB) stalked from outside well-positioned just off the leaders, went three then four wide on the turn, moved out a bit in mid-stretch, fought on for place over ATOMIC BLONDE (GER), who settled at the rear angling in, came off the fence racing two to three wide still at the back on the turn, came out a bit at the top of the stretch then was forced out by a rival in mid-stretch, kept on gamely but missed second. FEV ROVER (IRE) moved forward stalking the leader under light rating tactics from off the inside kept in about the three path, allowed that one a greater lead late up the backstretch before willingly edging nearer on the turn, drew to within a head nearing the three-eighths, took a narrow and brief lead past the five-sixteenths but was overtaken by the winner by the top of the stretch, ran on one-paced thereafter and was outfinished for placings. READY LADY angled in soon after the start, raced about mid-division saving ground on the turn, came out for the stretch run but needed more. MISS DRACARYS got away alertly and quickly went to the lead and clear, set the pace in hand shadowed by rivals early, edged away a bit late up the backstretch, was again challenged about midway on the turn, overtaken past the five-sixteenths and had no extra. FRACTIONAL TIMES UPDATED FOLLOWING REVIEW.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 11 6 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 92. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 114000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $9,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR RESTRICTED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 9, 2022 OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. ThreeY ear Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000, if for $47,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $40,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OWEN'S TOUR GUIDE emerged with the lead at the five furlong marker, opened up cruising up front through the turn, had a comfortable advantage straightening out for home and held safe under a well rationed front end win. GLORIANNIA stalked near the back of the pack on the rail in the beginning, improved up the fence running on the bend, hugged the rail gaining momentum at the top of the lane and was closing in late but could not reel in the loose frontrunner in time. PLEASURE'S GOLD was tracking between in the two path running down the backside, gamely chased the pacesetter on the turn hounded by horses on each side, continued to fight on in range of the leaders four wide driving to the wire and rallied to the finish to capture third. AMBASSADOR LUNA stalked outside four deep in the early going, made little advance when hard ridden three wide outside on the turn, angled out widest in the five path turning for home and offered a mild finish to close in for a minor share in the end. VERDEJO trailed between foes down the backstretch, was asked for more with runners on either side midpoint on the turn and finished up with interest to pass weary foes down the lane. STAR CANDY chased the pace on the rail down the back straight, was nudged on the fence making little gain inside throughout the turn and faded between rivals in the three path in the last sixteenth. TAP THE TITTLES tracked the loose pacesetter three deep outside down the backside, was roused three wide for more making little progress, shifted out to be four wide for the stretch drive and stopped in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 12 7F Turf CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 111600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIAM'S GIFT broke alertly, settled in just off and outside the leader pressing two to three wide, bid taking a narrow lead at the three-sixteenths, found a resilient foe inside and had to duel till late before edging away late. PRINCESSONAMISSION quickly moved forward to the lead inside setting the pace hounded by the eventual winner, was headed by that one near the three-sixteenths, fought on dueling inside regaining a very narrow advantage in mid-stretch but was outfinished in the late stages. COCO'S DREAM stalked from between the second flight early, moved nearer three to four wide late on the turn, got the nod for show after prolonged battle for that placing. GOOD NEWS MONEY moved forward inside tracking the leaders through the turn saving ground, came out at the three-sixteenths, lost the nod for show. JULIE'S MIST settled mid-pack between runners, was forced in and bumped a rival entering the turn, edged a bit nearer late on that bend, came out six wide turning into upper stretch, was carried in and ran on well. MRS. C settled outside at the rear, had to tap on the brakes running up on a retreating rival near the half, altered out at that juncture continuing well back four then five wide on the turn, fanned seven wide into upper stretch and with some run, drifted in, needed more late. SHAYSTOWN broke outwardly, chased briefly from outside then quickly dropped back four then three wide into and on the turn, angled nine wide into upper stretch and came again. NEOLITHIC NATION tracked about mid-pack inside, was bumped entering the turn, saved ground on that bend, ran on. ANNIA CORNIFICIA F broke a step slowly and awkwardly and was in tight, angled in bringing up the rear under early urging, saved ground, failed to menace. FLIP FLOPPIN FAST was off the pace outside runners three to four wide, faded. BEAUTIFUL AS YOU pursued from outside runners in the second flight racing three to four wide, dropped back and faded.
